text:
They're definitely on same spectrum, just different sides. I wish I had more time to expand on this, but the gist of my reasoning is that they'll eventually converge and connect in what Bill Gates called the "marketplace of content" in his constantly misinterpreted 1996 essay "Content is King."

A great example of what I'm talking about here would be Apple's App Store, which brings editorial content and UGC content (aka apps) together in one place. I was working on a roadmap to do this for Eventbrite, where event listings and editorial content existed side-by-side. And I'm proposing the same for Udemy.
